&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;REDDITCH &amp; BROMSGROVE LOCALITY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;COMMUNITY SERVICES HUB - BROMSGROVE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Community OT (Adaptations, Equipment and Housing)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;33.25 hours over 5 days per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Community Occupational Therapy Team (Adaptations, Equipment and Housing) provides a service for patients in their own homes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you: -      - aware of the Community OT role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;- Interested in assessing patients in their own homes for the: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;span&gt;provision of items of equipment &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;span&gt;major and minor adaptations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;span&gt;rehousing advice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Due to internal promotion we now require a new member of the team who should be a well-motivated therapist with some community experience pre or post registration, to join our well-established team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will:- &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ø&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span&gt;Have some experience of Community OT &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ø&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span&gt;Have knowledge of current legislation relating to housing and disability &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ø&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span&gt;Have some knowledge and experience of  adaptations and specialist equipment provision&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ø&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span&gt;Have a knowledge of the OT role within ‘housing’&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ø&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span&gt;Be able to work alone and as a member of the team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ø&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span&gt;Be extremely motivated, approachable with excellent communication skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ø&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span&gt;Be expected to manage a caseload of clients with varying needs and complexity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact:  Rowena Davis, Community OT Team Lead on 01527 488016 or email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;rowena.davis2@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
